[[ch07-overview-politically-incorrect-vs-rights]]
== Overview: Politically Incorrect vs Rights


This book is a conversation and not a textbook. No discussion here about itemizing the long list of various rights like the U.N. charter on human rights. Instead this discussion on rights is using the concept of being politically incorrect versus rights in popular culture that we all need to grapple with.


Fun fact, I'm the same age as Barack Obama, Jon Stewart and George Clooney. This makes me slightly younger than Bill Maher and Rush Limbaugh. Why does this matter? Because my guess is if people were asked if Obama was a Boomer or GenX then I'm guessing people would answer GenX. Whereas with Bill Maher and Rush Limbaugh people would definitely answer Boomer.

Technically I'm a Boomer being born in 1962 where GenX starts in 1964. However, any comparison between me and my brother born in 1958 regarding GenX vs Boomer would be similar where I would land in GenX and he in Boomer. There must have been something in the drinking water worldwide starting in the early 60s.

Rush Limbaugh and Bill Maher both had their careers take off in the 1990s. They both became popular for being "anti-woke" long before "anti-woke" was a thing. For Maher it was a TV show called, "Politically Incorrect" . Limbaugh started a radio career hating liberals for in part liberals being politically correct, or PC as he put it. Further they were both bullies. However, where Limbaugh fits the mold of a traditional "punch you in the face" bully, Maher was far more passive aggressive using comedy. Free speech was a common agenda for both and they both popularized free speech being part of pop culture even in 2026.

Benjamin Franklin famously said, "Your right to swing your fist ends at my face." Free speech advocates took that to mean that unless fists are flying then all speech is your right since no physical violence occurs. Franklin didn't believe that. Franklin was famously approached by a wealthy person to print slanderous gossip against one of the wealthy person's enemies in Franklin's newspaper. Franklin refused. The wealthy person then took to another newspaper to accuse Franklin of hypocrisy for not publishing his slander because Franklin promoted himself as a free speech advocate. He did this even after Franklin had offered to pay to publish the piece as a separate letter at no cost.

All this is to say that even today we treat rights as binary, black-and-white, even though that has never been the case. Yet still today that's how rights are promoted. You have the right to free speech, not we have the right to responsible use of speech. This is why New Democracy drops the use of the word "rights" and simply states we have responsibility for the use of speech.

Responsible speech is something I'm good at even though I'm neurodivergent. I have no diagnosis. I share characteristics with autism and other commonly known mental health disabilities. One such commonality is that I do lack social skills. Personal relationships are mostly nonexistent in my life. I live alone and have most of my life. Yet, guess wha my exaggerated human skill is? If you guessed social skills then you'd be correct. I excel at social interactions in group settings. 

I love public speaking. This really confuses people who try to get to know me. People get to know me in group settings and then are tripped up when my interpersonal skills suck.

My exaggerated skills matter because this capability is in part why I created New Democracy. As Spock said, "Each according to their own gifts." My gift of social skill gives me this capability to create New Democracy. As I also stated in the dedication of this book, tax payers like you made this possible by paying for twenty-two years of education.

Being Politically Incorrect is being lazy. Maher likes to whine that no one can keep track of all the changes happening daily.

My exaggerated social skills allow me to speak a personal language. Speaking to each person using their distinct language comes naturally to me. Each person's word usage for topics gets stored in memory without thought for me. This gives me an interpersonal social skill advantage over a normal person.

I long ago developed a diagnosis for people with limited personal language capability: weak character. For example, people who refuse to use preferred pronouns have weak character. Weak character is not a pejorative. People with weak character are just like me. They have social skill limitations. Mine are interpersonal, theirs are both interpersonal and social groups.

Here is a question, why would one purposely be weak? The person that one damages the most is themselves when being weak. One limits the set of people one can communicate with when being of weak character. Weak characters like Trump celebrate their weakness. I find this very odd.

This is what Benjamin Franklin had to say about bullies and free speech:

"I continued this ... Habit of expressing my self in Terms of modest Diffidence, never using when I advance any thing that may possibly be disputed, the Words, Certainly, undoudtedly, or any others that give
the Air of Positiveness to an Opinion; but rather say, I conceive, or I apprehend a Thing to be so or so, It appears to me, or I should think it so or so for such and such Reasons, or I imagine it to be so,
or it is so if I am not mistaken. This Habit I believe has been of great Advantage to me, when I have had occasion to inculate my Opinions and persuade Men into Measures that I have been from time to time engag'd in promoting. And as the chief ends of Conversation are to inform, or to be informed, to please or to persuade, I wish well meaning sensible Men would not lesson their Power of doing Good by a Positive assuming Manner that seldom fails to disgust, tends to create Opposition, and to defeat every one of those Purposes for which Speech was given us, to wit, giving or receiving Information, or Pleasure: For if you would inform, a positive dogmatical Manner in advancing your Sentiments, may provoke Contradiction and prevent candid Attention. If you wish Information and Improvement from the Knowledge of others and yet the same time express your self firmly fix'd in your present Opinions, modest sensible Men, who do not love Disputation, will probably leave you undisturb'd in the Possession of your Error; and such a Manner you can seldom hope to recommend your self in pleasing your Hearers, or to persuade those whose Concurrence
you desire."
                --Benjamin Franklin, The Autobiography of B.F.



In other words, sensitive people will leave bullies undisturbed when bullies bully. This means bullies lose all the benefits of being around sensitive people in their lives.

Plato observed this same principle in his book, "The Republic". Plato had two observations regarding sensitive people. First he was asked by a student if beating a prisoner was effective punishment. They were debating whether punishment could have a positive effect of preventing violent people from committing further violence. Plato famously responded, "Does beating a dog make it meaner or nicer?" Beating prisoners doesn't make them more sensitive about committing violence. Second Plato observed that moral people will never be politicians. The reason being is that politics is inherently corrupt and sensitive people will not compromise their principles.

All this is to say that bullies have weak characters. They really should be diagnosed the same as autism or any other neurodivergent people as having a mental disability. I realize things are more complicated in that I have no knowledge  how early childhood bullying common in many children growing up correlates with long-term bullies like Trump and Limbaugh.

I have a very strong character in group social settings. I'm the most word usage sensitive person in any room. This is because I naturally speak everyone's personal language. Bonus, this means I also learn to use "politically correct" terms of common culture. I can be the least offensive person you'll meet.

Bill Maher and Rush Limbaugh are not just lazy then. They are also disabled in the sense that they lack the capability to be sensitive. They compensate for this in different ways. Limbaugh by having been just a traditional bully. Maher by having a public campaign to limit sensitivity.

I bring all this up because rights as we see them today do not take into account capability. Some people are not capable of being sensitive. How does that stack up with free speech rights?

If you are a parent then you may be familiar with the nature versus nurture debate in psychology. As a parent what aspects of a child's personality can be shaped by nurture and what aspects are determined by nature?

Rights assume all aspects of everyone person's personality is nurtured. Another way to say this is that we are all born blank slates, tabula rasas, and free will means we are 100% responsible for every behavior trait we exhibit.

This is why rights must be done away with. It is important to note that rights grew out of religion. Religion also assumes all humans are tabula rasas and we are all responsible 100% for our actions and nature has no restrictions. Temptation yes, addiction no. Religion must also be discarded. 

Religion predates "nature versus nurture" science. Because religion predates science. Autism and neurodivergent behavior is fixed by nature. Just like addiction. Religion historically has treated mental health deficiencies as demonic possession and the devil's manipulations.

People having varied natural capability to conduct themselves socially so as to enforce rights is one reason rights need to be done away. In this sense Bill Maher and Rush Limbaugh were correct: not everyone has the same capability to be sensitive. Where they are politically incorrect is that this variation in capability should be enforced as some lowest-common-denominator social behavior. As Thomas Jefferson quipped, "As much as the public can tolerate." Although that was in response to using Federal funds for charity and not free speech expectations. So, politically correct speech should be implemented "as much as people can tolerate", yes and "least common people can use", no. Bill.

Irreni Society then opts for responsibilities replacing rights because individuals have widely varying capabilities to understand and implement them.

So far this discussion has been in the "nature versus nurture" domain. In addition, rights have other real world limitations. The most obvious limitation is our time. Bill Maher would argue convincingly, "Who has the time to keep up with all these new politically correct terms?" He's not wrong.

Let's put this in another context. Imagine a planet buster asteroid is on course for Earth. Predictions are that half of the human population will die on impact. Further imagine we only have a few short years to save as many people as possible. We also need to limit how many get saved based on an ability to keep people alive after the impact.

This is called life-boat ethics. The right to free speech becomes meaningless to the people who are about to die. Rights then can be thought of like an onion with many layers that protect a core seed. Survival is the core seed. At some point the quality of life layers kick in and this is where free speech resides as an outer layer.

Lifeboat ethics then is about making trade offs including who survives. In our planter buster asteroid scenario should we just attempt to save the most amount of people possible to survive the impact? Or perhaps set the number to save to some population that can survive for years of solar darkness due to ash covering the planet?

These kinds of dramatic lifeboat exercises can help bring answers into clarity. There exists a finite set of real-world resources to implement rights, including survival.

Irreni Society implements responsibilities as a tension. MGOs are a survival unit. MGOs can withdraw from management at any time. This is made possible in part because MGOs are required to have a year's supply of survival resources at all times when under management. What this means for our lifeboat asteroid scenario is that each MGO can withdraw from any larger discussion of responsibilities. This is to everyone's benefit. People making a sacrifice on behalf of others should only do so voluntarily. This is like when the Titanic sank and men agreed to the ethic, "women and children first" when it came to who got a spot on lifeboats. Everyone had the right to survive when the Titanic sank. Men had an equal right to a spot on a lifeboat. However, those men felt that the responsible thing was to put women and children first.

Irreni Society is women and children first in that it favors responsibility over rights. Responsibilities are voluntarily implemented in order to optimize outcomes. We don't want to force responsibility, known as oppression. Humans have been shown to do the least effort possible when forced to carry out responsibilities. This is why MGOs are free to opt out of management at any time.


Getting back to our onion example, responsibilities are layered and not isolated. Irreni Society layers responsibilities as layers of projects. Each project contract includes responsibilities each MGO joining the contract must enact. The more layers the more responsibilities. The more layers the more the ideological sum of the responsibilities add up too. As Thomas Jefferson said, each MGO will accept as much ideological responsibility as that MGO can take.


However, unlike an onion, Irreni Society project layers are more like the strata of millions of years of Earth rock than rings of a tree. There will be tectonic plates of large sets of distinct layers of responsibilities and within each tectonic plate there will be various groups of layers. Project layers are complicated where an onion or annual tree rings are not.

We will have all the rights laid out by the U.N. commission of human rights in Irreni Society. However, they will be project specific where largest projects have the most responsibilities we call rights today. The smallest project is survival. This project is called project zero. It has the least requirements for MGOs to implement, survival requirements we call rights today. The smallest set of responsibilities project is survival. This project is called project zero. It has the least requirements for MGOs to implement, survival requirements. Every MGO will have the seed responsibility of survival to start with. As an MGO demonstrates greater capability to meet more requirements then they may take on participation in larger projects of greater responsibilities that we call rights today.





















